txt_description: Refugee and Immigrant Students Empowered (RISE) was started in 2011 by Marielle Lovecchio, as part of the Nashville After Zone Alliance (NAZA) after school program system. RISE is now at four sites, serving 60 students from McMurray, Antioch, and Apollo middle schools. RISE students receive snacks, help with their homework, and the opportunity to practice their English skills in a small classroom environment. They are also introduced to a number of ëenhancementí activities, including painting, modern dance, culinary arts, photography, and much more! RISE students are in grades 5 through 8 and meet Monday through Friday from 4:00 to 6 p.m.
